9.8.19  11:22 am   I'm trying to write a book and I've had writer's block for the past year and a half. all I can come up with are little snippets of writing that I plan to put in later on in the story, but I'm stuck and can't write anything to continue the plot after what I have already. any advice?

      writers don't get blocks. if there is a block it means you have temporarily become a non-writer. but anyway, try writing something other than the plot, to go next. instead of trying to think of the 'plot' ...... the 'plot' is just a way to analyze things you already thought of. when you thought of them you were not trying to think of the plot. plot is like what happens when ice cream drips onto your hand bag. plot plot ...... catch it before it hits your pants next
